      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "7141507136ad08f6",
      "text": "Many teachers were teaching online for the first time because of Corona and had no time to prepare methodically. What adjustments are necessary when moving the classroom from the school building to the Internet - depending on the level?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "6726ff8809812209",
      "text": "I believe that moving the classroom to the Internet cannot be done without some losses. Distance learning probably works well when learners and teachers have a sustainable relationship. And if there are certain technical prerequisites on both sides - stable Internet, competent handling of a digital learning platform. But my experience from online learning is that sometimes less is more. Especially with adult learners, it doesn't always have to be a live video conference. Books are still important learning media. And you can take them outside, too. Many learners have welcomed the flexible scheduling. A good balance between presence and independence is important.\n\n"
