      "text": "Distance learning could bring the heterogeneity of family backgrounds, and therefore possibly inequality of opportunity, more into the open. Recent studies also show that children also suffered greatly psychologically from the shutdown and spent less time learning overall. Schools will likely need some time to tend to these wounds. The fear of a next shutdown could also lead to increased practice of self-organized learning in the future, even during periods of attendance. As a preventative measure, so to speak.\n\n"
