      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "eb2d5d20ae5b0b77",
      "text": "There has been such a push as a result of the shutdown, but it has been implemented in different ways. But apart from digitization, it was at least as important during the shutdown to have a feel for the situation of learners, their resilience and ability to concentrate. I heard from students that they had to work harder than usual because of the many assignments during distance learning. Many have found the focus on the screen challenging. Teachers and learners alike have had to gain new experience in what the right dose and amount of material is. When I look at the students, I think that the teachers of tomorrow are already well-versed in digitalization and also have a variety of methods in their baggage.\n\n"
