      "id": "5a57420d8474a336",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "5a57420d8474a336",
        "text": "Since peripatetic teaching is possible in a normal 45- or 90-minute lesson, any teacher can work in this format and integrate other teaching methods along the way, such as discussion and conversation methods. Important: \"Spectacular\" places like zoos or archaeological sites are often not at all ideal for peripatetic teaching because they are already \"through-didacticized.\" And logistically difficult to reach. In peripatetic teaching, the journey is the destination. Walking areas near the school that have thematic affinity but are \"unobtrusive\" are optimal. A walk along a country lane can be more inspiring than a visit to the zoo."
